WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:03.002
<i>Previously on "Being Mary Jane..."</i>

00:03.436 --> 00:08.208
- You okay with me having kids?
- Yeah, I like kids.

00:08.508 --> 00:12.245
Is that your driver? Did you tip him?
Looks like he's waiting for something.

00:12.645 --> 00:14.814
I should've known Old Spice man
was your type.

00:14.881 --> 00:17.450
First of all,
you wouldn't know what my type is.

00:17.717 --> 00:20.620
And second of all,
we never said we were exclusive.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.155
I'm done trying to figure you out.

00:23.256 --> 00:24.524
It's so lonely.

00:27.694 --> 00:29.062
And I'm so tired.

00:29.129 --> 00:30.230
So stop running.

00:30.697 --> 00:32.932
- Take a risk.
- So you forgive me?

00:32.999 --> 00:34.567
They would never said it out loud.

00:34.634 --> 00:38.738
But the assumption is there can only be
one black woman at the table.

00:38.805 --> 00:42.008
I think there's room for both of us.

00:42.342 --> 00:45.211
- What do you say? Are you with me?
- Yeah, I'm with you.

00:45.278 --> 00:47.881
I built that charity from nothing.

00:49.649 --> 00:51.251
It was my brand.

00:51.618 --> 00:53.052
Now it's poisoned.

00:53.119 --> 00:55.155
This is not how I wanted it to happen.

00:55.221 --> 00:56.689
Kara, she mentored me.

00:56.756 --> 01:00.160
I wasn't gonna let her whole world
blow up without telling her first.

01:00.226 --> 01:04.697
I brought you into my world, Mary Jane.
Me. I got you this damn job!

01:05.064 --> 01:06.299
What are you doing here?

01:06.366 --> 01:08.535
- I'm the new senior producer.
- Producer? Here?

01:08.802 --> 01:10.470
When Ronda Sales calls and invites you

01:10.537 --> 01:12.472
on the biggest morning show
in the country,

01:13.173 --> 01:14.407
you answer.

01:27.487 --> 01:28.888
A private elevator?

01:29.255 --> 01:31.057
A killer view of Manhattan.

01:32.826 --> 01:36.296
- I feel like I'm home already.
- Too bad it's not for sale.

01:36.830 --> 01:40.600
How does my little brother, who used to
twirl signs on a street corner,

01:40.667 --> 01:41.734
afford this?

01:41.801 --> 01:43.970
My old boss in L.A. hooked me up

01:44.037 --> 01:46.906
with one of the best real estate firms
in New York.

01:46.973 --> 01:48.842
And I am killing it right now.

01:48.908 --> 01:50.043
In six months?

01:50.376 --> 01:52.512
Have you even had time
to build up a clientele?

01:52.579 --> 01:55.815
I just tell people my sister
is about to be the next Ronda Sales.

01:55.882 --> 01:57.517
I wouldn't count on that.

01:58.351 --> 02:00.487
What happened?
I thought the deal was all set.

02:00.553 --> 02:02.522
Justin happened, for starters.

02:02.589 --> 02:03.790
Okay, who's Justin?

02:04.390 --> 02:05.859
Long tragic story.

02:05.925 --> 02:07.427
But anyway...

02:07.494 --> 02:09.195
How much does something like this cost?

02:09.562 --> 02:10.964
- Fifteen million.
- What?

02:11.030 --> 02:13.132
Yeah. We're not in ATL anymore, 'Letta.

02:13.199 --> 02:15.101
Four percent of 15 million is...

02:15.168 --> 02:19.272
Six hundred thousand dollars.
My God, did I just say that?

02:19.606 --> 02:21.241
- Yeah. That's...
- I did.

02:21.307 --> 02:23.543
That's a lot of money,
but it doesn't afford this.

02:23.610 --> 02:27.347
It belongs to a client. I'm managing it
while they're out of the country.

02:27.413 --> 02:31.417
Tell me, have there been any naked girls
on that white couch?

02:31.484 --> 02:33.586
It's not like that, 'Letta.
I promise you.

02:33.653 --> 02:36.923
Look. Can we just focus
on what you're looking for?

02:36.990 --> 02:40.426
You have to be out of that hotel
pretty soon.

02:40.994 --> 02:45.265
So what are we talking?
You want a two-bedroom, large kitchen?

02:45.331 --> 02:47.867
- We're talking this. I want this.
- This.

02:48.134 --> 02:49.402
But with a lot less zeros.

02:57.110 --> 02:59.112
I should've listened to you about Ronda.

02:59.512 --> 03:01.848
I swear I wake up thinking about it
every morning.

03:02.682 --> 03:04.183
That's water under the bridge.

03:05.285 --> 03:08.021
We have a much bigger problem now.
Freakin' Boys Club.

03:08.321 --> 03:11.190
Justin had a knack
for sucking up to the higher-ups.

03:11.591 --> 03:13.426
Did the same damn thing in Atlanta.

03:14.661 --> 03:15.762
Jackass.

03:15.828 --> 03:19.032
I hustled my way into this network
so I could be promoted to nightly news.

03:19.098 --> 03:21.200
- And you will.
- Not without big stories.

03:21.267 --> 03:23.937
Still no word about covering
the Supreme Court nominee?

03:24.237 --> 03:27.340
With Justin here, Garrett won't even look
in my damn direction.

03:27.907 --> 03:31.611
I was looking to make history here,
be the first woman to run this show.

03:31.678 --> 03:34.714
But Mr. Smooth Operator wants it
just as bad as I do.

03:35.048 --> 03:36.749
It's 2008, all over again.

03:36.816 --> 03:39.786
I'm Hillary, and the fine-ass black man
is trying to kick my damn ass.

03:40.086 --> 03:42.188
So, we figure out
how to get killer stories.

03:42.255 --> 03:43.389
Where's Natalie?

03:43.957 --> 03:46.659
I don't know. Editing, maybe? Why?

03:46.726 --> 03:49.829
We got an exclusive with New York's
second baseman, Orlando Lagos.

03:49.896 --> 03:51.030
Is Natalie covering it?

03:51.097 --> 03:53.299
No, Aaron is.
So we gotta bump her segment.

03:53.366 --> 03:56.402
This cooking segment
Kara spent all morning working on?

03:56.469 --> 03:59.806
Yes. Look, it's a solid segment.
I'm sure it'll come back around.

04:05.411 --> 04:07.046
It's an app called "Wantagwan."

04:07.113 --> 04:09.582
You can take video,
pictures, add filters,

04:09.649 --> 04:11.584
and your followers can leave comments.

04:11.651 --> 04:13.553
And how is this different from Snapchat?

04:14.087 --> 04:17.924
Way more emojis. Facebook's gonna
eventually buy it for billions.

04:18.224 --> 04:21.394
Being up on the latest apps is sexy.
It's current.

04:21.728 --> 04:23.029
Appeals to the younger demo.

04:23.296 --> 04:24.964
We can use it to promote the show.

04:25.031 --> 04:27.834
Our viewers love it
when we try out the new gadgets.

04:28.368 --> 04:30.169
Great idea. What else we got?

04:30.236 --> 04:34.140
How about the teacher caught on video
berating the second grader?

04:34.440 --> 04:35.908
She apologized, didn't she?

04:35.975 --> 04:38.144
They're saying
it wasn't an isolated incident.

04:38.211 --> 04:39.646
American kids are too coddled.

04:39.712 --> 04:42.148
Rest of the world is beating us.
We need to toughen up.

04:42.215 --> 04:45.084
I think it's more complicated
than "tough love."

04:45.151 --> 04:47.687
This is an Ivy League educated woman,

04:47.754 --> 04:50.623
and she was teaching predominantly
underprivileged kids.

04:50.690 --> 04:52.692
Mostly black and Latino kids.

04:53.292 --> 04:55.595
The little girl in question,
she was black.

04:55.662 --> 04:58.665
Well, plenty to debate.
That much is obvious.

05:00.466 --> 05:01.634
What do you think, Ronda?

05:01.701 --> 05:04.170
I agree, but I like Natalie's take on it.

05:04.237 --> 05:06.305
She should do it,
since her segment was cut.

05:06.372 --> 05:08.141
But isn't Natalie covering the app?

05:08.608 --> 05:10.243
I do already have three segments.

05:10.576 --> 05:12.612
She can handle this one just fine.

05:12.679 --> 05:15.748
She also has the interview style
we're looking for.

05:16.616 --> 05:17.817
Yeah, you're right.

05:19.018 --> 05:21.587
Natalie will do the teacher story
with Justin.

05:21.654 --> 05:23.956
And Mary Jane,
you can take the "Wantagwan" piece.

05:24.624 --> 05:26.426
- And Kara, you can produce it.
- Yes.

05:28.294 --> 05:29.495
Good.

05:31.597 --> 05:33.066
Mary Jane. Come on in.

05:37.336 --> 05:41.507
Garret, I just want you to know
it's important to me to do a good job.

05:42.041 --> 05:43.276
And you are.

05:43.342 --> 05:46.713
In the meeting, it sounded like you had
a problem with my interview style.

05:47.814 --> 05:49.282
It's nothing against you.

05:49.582 --> 05:54.020
We've been doing some in-house
evaluations of on air talent...

05:54.087 --> 05:55.755
I don't mean to interrupt,

05:56.422 --> 06:00.193
but can I assume that Justin
is a part of that "we?"

06:00.626 --> 06:02.195
It's part of the show's makeover.

06:03.663 --> 06:06.432
So Justin has a problem
with my interview style?

06:11.804 --> 06:13.005
Can you grab Justin for me?

06:15.274 --> 06:16.809
It's better if he explains.

06:17.076 --> 06:20.780
Can I just say I really feel
like these evaluations should be unbiased

06:20.847 --> 06:23.983
and I worry that with Justin,
it can, you know...

06:25.084 --> 06:28.121
Hey, man. Would you mind
telling Mary Jane what you told me?

06:28.421 --> 06:29.489
Sure.

06:29.555 --> 06:32.692
I reviewed all the work
of each of the correspondents.

06:32.759 --> 06:36.095
And since you're new,
I watched a segment from SNC.

06:36.362 --> 06:39.132
I believe this is your interview
with Elizabeth Foy.

06:39.198 --> 06:42.468
Right, yeah.
Went viral, and audiences loved it.

06:44.437 --> 06:46.305
I found your approach
a little concerning.

06:47.573 --> 06:49.842
<i>It gets the politics out of the way,</i>

06:49.909 --> 06:53.045
<i>and allows the parents to decide
what's best for their child.</i>

06:53.112 --> 06:55.681
<i>It's interesting
that you mention politics,</i>

06:55.748 --> 06:58.584
<i>because some are arguing
your best-selling book is published</i>

06:58.651 --> 07:01.954
<i>by a foundation that supports
neo-racists authors.</i>

07:02.955 --> 07:04.357
You derail the conversation

07:04.423 --> 07:07.693
and promote your own agenda.
And there's no subtlety in your approach.

07:09.495 --> 07:11.631
<i>We're both fighting to be heard
and fighting</i>

07:11.697 --> 07:13.466
<i>to be taken seriously and to be seen.</i>

07:13.800 --> 07:16.936
<i>So when it comes down to it,
when I look at you,</i>

07:18.571 --> 07:20.006
<i>I see an ugly black woman too.</i>

07:21.340 --> 07:24.443
That's an ambush.
I mean, worse still, race baiting.

07:24.710 --> 07:27.914
I think your demeanor is cold.
It's judgmental. It's haughty.

07:28.981 --> 07:32.151
I don't think that's what our viewers
want with their morning coffee.

07:32.218 --> 07:34.887
Mary Jane, we all know
you have charisma and charm.

07:34.954 --> 07:36.389
And that works for the lighter pieces.

07:36.455 --> 07:38.357
It's the serious interviews...

07:39.525 --> 07:40.993
I just don't think they're for you.

07:54.707 --> 07:58.477
- This was supposed to be my comeback.
- It still is, Mary Jane.

07:58.544 --> 08:00.580
No. See what I am up against.

08:00.646 --> 08:02.215
All you need is one great story.

08:02.515 --> 08:06.152
All the great stories
are assigned to someone else.

08:06.519 --> 08:09.021
Then give them a story
that only you can do.

08:11.757 --> 08:12.925
Hey.

08:16.896 --> 08:18.030
Hello.

08:19.198 --> 08:20.466
You've barely eaten.

08:20.867 --> 08:22.535
What is all this, anyway?

08:23.402 --> 08:24.770
Old story ideas.

08:24.837 --> 08:27.173
Things I covered,
things I never got to cover.

08:27.240 --> 08:30.977
It's low tech, I know,
but I'm hoping something sparks an idea.

08:31.043 --> 08:32.745
You brought all of this from Atlanta?

08:32.812 --> 08:36.115
Yeah, that's the first thing I'd grab
if the house caught fire.

08:37.049 --> 08:38.117
Are you sure?

08:40.152 --> 08:41.888
What about this?

08:42.588 --> 08:43.656
Nick?

08:43.723 --> 08:46.893
No. Nick's been a constant companion,
but no. Nick can be replaced.

08:49.161 --> 08:50.129
Well,

08:51.998 --> 08:53.132
I'll leave you to it.

09:09.515 --> 09:11.450
<i>Feel like I'm being included
in this family.</i>

09:11.517 --> 09:13.252
<i>And then this bitch cornered me.</i>

09:13.319 --> 09:15.755
<i>She got the nerve to get in my face.</i>

09:15.821 --> 09:18.991
<i>Well, I can't hit my father. But
I'll definitely hit her because...</i>

09:19.058 --> 09:20.960
Are you enjoying your tea party
over there?

09:21.761 --> 09:23.029
You'd be drinking tea too

09:23.095 --> 09:25.998
if it wasn't for a petty,
300-year-old rebellion.

09:26.065 --> 09:29.468
No, coffee is the only way to go.
And black, as it should be.

09:29.535 --> 09:31.804
All right, Malcolm X-presso.

09:33.339 --> 09:36.142
<i>-How can you be so selfish?
- I'm not selfish!</i>

09:38.644 --> 09:39.612
Jesus.

09:40.579 --> 09:41.647
I'm sorry. Is it too loud?

09:43.616 --> 09:46.452
Sorry, I'm feeling
little claustrophobic in this hotel room.

09:47.420 --> 09:49.322
Really gotta get serious
about finding a new place.

09:50.222 --> 09:51.657
Do you know what? I do too.

09:52.158 --> 09:53.826
My sublet's up soon.

09:54.293 --> 09:56.862
My brother's showing me a listing
tomorrow afternoon.

09:58.898 --> 10:01.300
But New York is so expensive.

10:01.367 --> 10:02.601
- So expensive.
- Right?

10:08.441 --> 10:10.943
We're not actually having
this conversation now, are we?

10:11.344 --> 10:15.815
No, 'cause it's way too early
for us to be even thinking about this.

10:17.049 --> 10:18.017
Right?

10:18.985 --> 10:19.952
Right.

10:20.419 --> 10:22.154
I mean, you haven't met my kids.

10:23.456 --> 10:24.457
Exactly.

10:24.724 --> 10:26.459
And I haven't farted in front of you yet.

10:26.726 --> 10:28.027
Well, you don't need to.

10:35.701 --> 10:36.869
I love this.

10:37.269 --> 10:38.838
What are you watching?

10:38.904 --> 10:40.740
This? This is brilliant.

10:41.040 --> 10:43.809
If America does one thing great,
it is reality TV.

10:44.677 --> 10:47.313
You see this guy,
he's a retired point guard.

10:47.380 --> 10:49.582
He has multiple children
from many different moms.

10:49.648 --> 10:52.284
I'll guess: They're all forced
to live in the house together.

10:52.351 --> 10:54.820
- It's genius!
- It gives me anxiety.

10:54.887 --> 10:56.956
They are fighting over
his endorsement money.

10:57.023 --> 10:58.758
It gets pretty ugly.

10:59.358 --> 11:01.060
I'm pretty sure my niece watches this.

11:04.296 --> 11:06.565
Goodness gracious.
Who is the ratchet one?

11:06.866 --> 11:09.702
Mercedes. She's the star.
She has five children.

11:11.670 --> 11:13.272
Why do you watch this garbage again?

11:13.672 --> 11:14.807
Garbage?

11:15.408 --> 11:18.177
Let me tell you,
I get so much material from this.

11:18.244 --> 11:21.280
I consider this my Master's
in American culture.

11:21.847 --> 11:23.416
And that's a damn shame.

11:23.482 --> 11:24.717
You can judge if you want,

11:25.217 --> 11:28.454
but when Mercedes is on the screen
you cannot change the channel.

11:28.521 --> 11:30.723
<i>She is trying to get in
between the relationship</i>

11:30.790 --> 11:33.159
<i>with my father,
and that's my father, not yours.</i>

11:33.492 --> 11:34.927
<i>Find your daddy somewhere.</i>

11:36.562 --> 11:39.965
What does the league MVP do after
winning the Pennant three years in a row?

11:40.566 --> 11:41.801
Go for a fourth?

11:41.867 --> 11:45.104
<i>You're not gonna pull a Ken Griffey Jr.
on us and do a one and done, are you?</i>

11:45.171 --> 11:48.974
I had him on my fantasy team
for three years. Solid every year.

11:49.909 --> 11:51.811
<i>It's a dream come true being in New York.</i>

11:51.877 --> 11:54.847
<i>- I'm just enjoying the ride.
- We're gonna enjoy the ride with you.</i>

11:54.914 --> 11:57.383
If Aaron can't pull
a retirement announcement out of him,

11:57.883 --> 11:58.951
no one can.

11:59.018 --> 12:02.388
I don't think he's gonna say much else.
The guy's got three standard answers.

12:02.655 --> 12:03.622
Okay, wrap it up.

12:03.989 --> 12:05.591
<i>We'll be right back with Orlando Lagos,</i>

12:05.658 --> 12:07.827
<i>who's gonna show us
the key to his signature swing.</i>

12:09.528 --> 12:11.831
- He looks good too.
- He does.

12:13.232 --> 12:15.968
- You have fun doing this?
- It's the best job in the world.

12:16.035 --> 12:17.703
Yeah, how did you get started?

12:18.070 --> 12:20.573
<i>Started working
for this local TV station.</i>

12:20.906 --> 12:24.176
<i>One of the guys didn't show up one day.
They threw me in front of the camera,</i>

12:24.243 --> 12:26.178
<i>and that's pretty much
the end of the story.</i>

12:26.245 --> 12:27.446
- That's great.
- Yeah.

12:30.549 --> 12:34.086
Orlando. Hi. My name is Kara Lynch.
I'm a producer here.

12:34.153 --> 12:35.354
Hi.

12:35.421 --> 12:37.490
Can I talk to you for a minute
in private?

12:38.257 --> 12:40.726
These are my boys.
You can say what you gotta say.

12:40.793 --> 12:43.095
Tell you what,
I have a break in about an hour.

12:43.162 --> 12:45.364
Why don't you meet me
at the bar around the corner?

12:45.431 --> 12:47.032
- We can make that happen.
- Yeah?

12:47.867 --> 12:49.001
In private.

12:49.902 --> 12:51.036
Boys...

12:55.341 --> 12:56.642
<i>God, are you kidding me?</i>

12:56.709 --> 12:58.711
<i>Mercedes,
need you to stop spending money!</i>

12:58.777 --> 13:01.514
"Family Brawlers?" Seriously?

13:01.580 --> 13:04.884
- Girl, it's so bad, it's good.
- God.

13:06.118 --> 13:09.021
<i>Here comes Carmen
talkin' outta the side of her neck...</i>

13:09.088 --> 13:11.957
Yeah, that's her little catchphrase.

13:12.558 --> 13:14.894
What do you think
about bringing her on the show?

13:14.960 --> 13:17.229
What? Mercedes Wilkerson? On live TV?

13:17.296 --> 13:21.567
Yeah. Think about it.
This is a story only I can do.

13:22.134 --> 13:24.770
If I can find a way
to relate to this woman,

13:24.837 --> 13:28.707
get her on my side, humanize her
a little bit, it could be good.

13:28.774 --> 13:31.677
- That woman's a damn train wreck.
- She's playing a character.

13:31.744 --> 13:34.013
I'm sure there's a real person
under there.

13:34.079 --> 13:35.548
And I'm pretty sure I can find it.

13:35.614 --> 13:38.517
So you wanna turn your app story
into a hard-hitting interview?

13:38.784 --> 13:40.920
She could use the app during the show
and bring in

13:40.986 --> 13:43.255
that young demo Garrett wants so badly.

13:43.956 --> 13:45.224
Come on.

13:45.291 --> 13:47.226
Justin's gonna shoot this down faster

13:47.293 --> 13:49.795
than you can say
"talkin' out the side your neck."

13:49.862 --> 13:53.432
I thought about that.
I think I figured out a way around that.

13:55.367 --> 13:58.404
So the weight loss special
rounds out the 8 a.m. block.

13:58.470 --> 14:00.406
- Any pitches for 9 a.m.?
- I have one.

14:00.472 --> 14:01.607
Yes.

14:01.674 --> 14:05.110
How about an interview with the star
of the reality series "Family Brawlers?"

14:05.744 --> 14:07.546
- Mercedes Wilkerson?
- Yes.

14:07.613 --> 14:10.549
Isn't that the crazy woman
that put her boyfriend in the hospital

14:10.616 --> 14:12.184
with a toaster oven or something?

14:12.251 --> 14:14.186
I think it was a microwave.

14:14.253 --> 14:16.222
She's definitely a bit of wild child.

14:16.288 --> 14:20.192
But she tripled the demo when
she appeared on talk shows in Atlanta,

14:20.259 --> 14:21.994
Los Angeles and Chicago.

14:22.061 --> 14:24.630
She's coming out with a new swimwear line
we can feature,

14:24.697 --> 14:26.899
which is a bridge to our 18 to 34 demo

14:26.966 --> 14:29.101
and cross promotion
with our sister network.

14:30.169 --> 14:32.404
- The suits will love that.
- Yeah.

14:32.471 --> 14:34.073
- Who should do it?
- How about Ronda?

14:36.609 --> 14:37.676
No.

14:38.644 --> 14:40.713
No, that's not really my brand.

14:40.779 --> 14:42.014
Come on, now. Come on.

14:42.081 --> 14:45.150
She's very popular with the app
Mary Jane is covering.

14:45.217 --> 14:47.920
Yeah, Mary Jane, you did a good job
with that hip-hop artist.

14:47.987 --> 14:50.022
Okay. Mercedes is a powder keg.

14:50.456 --> 14:52.625
We don't need Mary Jane
to light that fuse.

14:52.691 --> 14:54.893
Let's remember
who our intended audience is.

14:54.960 --> 14:56.195
Then you produce it.

14:57.696 --> 15:02.101
Justin doesn't know the show,
so I don't...

15:02.434 --> 15:07.206
Great. He'll approach it with fresh eyes
and find an interesting angle.

