31:45.103 --> 31:46.437
I'm not trying to mess that up.

31:47.171 --> 31:48.740
You got people looking out for you.

31:50.108 --> 31:52.176
- I like it. That's important.
- It is.

31:53.244 --> 31:56.414
I'll arrange it so that
you can show yourself the place.

31:56.481 --> 31:59.183
But if you like it,
you gotta let me know ASAP.

31:59.250 --> 32:02.120
I already got a couple clients
looking at it, chomping at the bit.

32:02.520 --> 32:03.688
All right.

32:04.522 --> 32:05.757
Nice meeting you, Greta.

32:06.557 --> 32:07.659
You can go.

32:11.229 --> 32:13.665
I practically exploded on live TV.

32:14.299 --> 32:16.034
Pretty sure my mom had a stroke.

32:16.301 --> 32:18.670
For what it's worth,
I thought it was pretty funny.

32:21.105 --> 32:24.008
This place will make me
forget all of my troubles.

32:26.077 --> 32:27.211
What do you think?

32:29.280 --> 32:30.381
It's nice.

32:30.682 --> 32:31.849
It's nice?

32:32.383 --> 32:33.685
This place is wavy.

32:36.854 --> 32:39.324
Don't tell me you're serious
about the radiator thing.

32:41.159 --> 32:44.595
No, it's cool. I'll hold out until
I find a place with clanky radiators.

32:45.630 --> 32:46.597
Mary Jane...

32:47.198 --> 32:50.068
If you like this place, buy it.

32:50.868 --> 32:54.872
- But buy it for you.
- Yeah, I am. I'm just thinking ahead.

32:55.340 --> 32:58.609
Are you, though?
I'm sensing some urgency here.

32:58.676 --> 33:03.648
No, I know you're not moving in
right away, but you might one day, right?

33:04.982 --> 33:07.852
I can't even consider that question
until you've met my kids.

33:08.119 --> 33:09.454
No, I get that.

33:09.954 --> 33:12.423
But I'm about to spend a small fortune
on this place,

33:12.890 --> 33:14.425
and I'd really like your opinion.

33:15.526 --> 33:19.464
My opinion is you're buying this place
for two, not for one.

33:21.265 --> 33:23.568
Okay, I'll just put
the rest of my life on hold

33:23.634 --> 33:25.703
until you're ready
to have a conversation.

33:25.770 --> 33:28.373
MJ, that's the exact opposite
to what I've just said.

33:29.707 --> 33:31.976
Look, I say "not now"
and you hear "not ever."

33:33.511 --> 33:35.747
I've had way too many
dead-end relationships, Lee.

33:36.180 --> 33:37.148
I'm over it.

33:38.082 --> 33:40.051
No more games, okay?

33:41.486 --> 33:43.321
Are you in or out?

33:44.856 --> 33:47.358
I've told you I'm not moving in with you.

33:52.029 --> 33:53.097
Fine.

33:54.999 --> 33:56.100
Get the hell out.

33:59.103 --> 34:00.838
- Mary Jane...
- I mean it, Lee. Leave.

34:02.073 --> 34:03.107
Leave!

34:13.217 --> 34:15.319
- Hey.
- Everybody's staring at me.

34:16.320 --> 34:18.055
Have you seen your Twitter feed?

34:18.122 --> 34:21.092
Hell no. I've been avoiding
the Internet like the plague.

34:21.159 --> 34:23.528
Well, your rant went viral, Missy.

34:23.594 --> 34:25.596
- Let me see that.
- Look at the Twitter feed.

34:25.663 --> 34:29.167
All the pundits
are talking about double consciousness.

34:29.434 --> 34:33.137
Van Jones schooled a panel
about how black professionals

34:33.204 --> 34:35.072
have to be one way
around their white colleagues

34:35.139 --> 34:36.974
and another way
around other black people.

34:37.708 --> 34:39.844
And Melissa Harris Perry
wants an interview.

34:39.911 --> 34:41.279
- Shut up.
- Yes.

34:41.345 --> 34:43.848
And there's also
a "Huffington Post" editorial

34:43.915 --> 34:46.417
talking about
"dropping the mask" at work.

34:47.418 --> 34:50.922
So you said you wanted to do
something meaningful, and you did.

34:50.988 --> 34:53.658
So we need to celebrate tonight.
You gotta call Lee.

34:54.258 --> 34:55.393
About that...

34:55.860 --> 34:57.028
What did you do?

34:57.829 --> 34:59.030
I'll tell you later.

35:01.499 --> 35:02.533
Okay.

35:02.834 --> 35:04.135
Celebrate my ratchet.

35:04.402 --> 35:05.636
Celebrate.

35:13.110 --> 35:16.781
I suppose congratulations are in order.
You and Mercedes broke the Internet.

35:17.114 --> 35:20.685
Yet, I feel like I owe you an apology
for what I said on air. I'm so sorry.

35:21.085 --> 35:24.055
No need to apologize for being a hit.
We should capitalize on it.

35:24.655 --> 35:26.924
Ronda came up with a great way
to do just that.

35:26.991 --> 35:28.226
- She did?
- Yeah.

35:28.292 --> 35:31.596
She suggested you become
our resident web correspondent.

35:33.498 --> 35:35.933
So instead of being on on-air,
I'll be on the Internet?

35:36.534 --> 35:38.503
Hey, the web is the future, right?

36:29.554 --> 36:30.521
Hey.

36:32.023 --> 36:32.957
Hey.

36:35.893 --> 36:36.994
TV's off.

36:38.596 --> 36:40.798
New episode
of "Family Brawlers" is about to start.

36:42.466 --> 36:43.534
I thought we broke up.

36:44.502 --> 36:45.469
We did?

36:47.071 --> 36:48.039
When?

36:48.339 --> 36:49.874
When I told you to get out.

36:50.808 --> 36:51.976
Well, we had an argument.

36:52.376 --> 36:54.946
You told me to leave, so I did.
It's what adults do.

36:55.680 --> 36:57.214
We argue, and we work it out.

36:58.316 --> 37:01.586
Plus, I thought I'd give you some time
to tell me what's really going on.

37:04.989 --> 37:07.358
- That place was dope.
- This is Manhattan.

37:07.858 --> 37:10.061
It's an island full of dope apartments.

37:13.531 --> 37:15.166
Why are you suddenly trying to rush this?

37:17.535 --> 37:18.970
I turn 40 in two months.

37:20.104 --> 37:21.072
Join the club.

37:23.741 --> 37:25.610
I turn 40, and I imagined

37:27.345 --> 37:28.713
where I'd be, and...

37:31.148 --> 37:36.621
I guess I just tried to race to get there
before the clock struck 12.

37:37.622 --> 37:39.056
So, this had nothing to do with me.

37:39.523 --> 37:41.993
It was just about you
checking off some boxes.

37:45.229 --> 37:47.932
Why is settling down
such an accomplishment in America?

37:50.301 --> 37:51.435
I don't know. You tell me.

37:53.604 --> 37:54.538
Hey.

37:55.573 --> 37:57.608
Forty is the new thirty.

37:58.909 --> 38:00.745
It's the new 20
when you're a black woman.

38:01.178 --> 38:03.047
- Especially one that looks like you.
- Stop.

38:09.020 --> 38:11.088
Still sucks
to let that beautiful place go.

38:11.155 --> 38:14.825
No, not at all. The central heating
would've killed you eventually.

38:16.861 --> 38:18.896
Plus, I don't want my kids
breathing that in.

38:20.564 --> 38:22.867
They're gonna come visit
for spring break.

38:23.601 --> 38:26.037
They wanted to go to Spain,
but I want you to meet them.

38:30.608 --> 38:33.477
Let go of what you think
is supposed to happen.

38:35.579 --> 38:36.547
Just let it be.

38:43.988 --> 38:45.022
Come here.

38:53.731 --> 38:55.332
So are we watching this or not?

38:56.634 --> 38:57.601
- Yeah.
- Great.

39:01.639 --> 39:02.907
Just give me a minute.

39:25.596 --> 39:26.797
What are you doing here?

39:27.832 --> 39:29.467
Every win must be celebrated.

39:36.774 --> 39:40.010
I don't gotta worry about Daekwan.
I don't gotta worry about Lucretia.

39:40.077 --> 39:41.912
I don't gotta worry about Aunt Shaunae.

39:41.979 --> 39:45.583
I don't gotta worry about
none of them, especially Carmen...

39:46.317 --> 39:47.685
<i>that's not even his daughter.</i>

39:48.986 --> 39:50.521
Did you really think we'd broken up?

39:52.823 --> 39:55.025
Yeah, I did.

39:56.293 --> 39:58.295
Well, congratulations.

39:59.530 --> 40:01.699
You're about to celebrate your 40th.

40:02.833 --> 40:05.569
And it looks like
you might be in a real relationship.

40:05.970 --> 40:06.937
What?
